### Escenario 1: Desarrollo Local (Todo en localhost)

```bash
# provider/.env
PROVIDER_URL=http://localhost:5009
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://oidc_user:password@localhost:5437/oidc_db
NODE_ENV=development

# backend/.env
PROVIDER_EXTERNAL_URL=http://localhost:5009
OIDC_CLIENT_ID=local-client
OIDC_CLIENT_SECRET=local-secret
OIDC_CALLBACK_URL=http://localhost:4009/auth/callback
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:3008
BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:4009
SESSION_SECRET=dev-secret
TRUST_PROXY=0
```

### Escenario 2: Producción - Servidor Único con Nginx

```bash
# provider/.env
PROVIDER_URL=https://auth.acceleralia.com
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://oidc_user:PASSWORD@localhost:5432/oidc_db
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=8080

# backend/.env
PROVIDER_EXTERNAL_URL=https://auth.acceleralia.com
PROVIDER_INTERNAL_URL=http://localhost:8080
OIDC_CLIENT_ID=acceleralia-client
OIDC_CLIENT_SECRET=SECRET_32_CHARS_MIN
OIDC_CALLBACK_URL=https://api.acceleralia.com/auth/callback
FRONTEND_URL=https://app.acceleralia.com
BACKEND_URL=https://api.acceleralia.com
SESSION_SECRET=SECRET_32_CHARS_MIN
SESSION_DOMAIN=.acceleralia.com
TRUST_PROXY=1
PORT=8080
```

### Escenario 3: Producción - Servidores Separados

```bash
# provider/.env (en servidor de auth)
PROVIDER_URL=https://auth.acceleralia.com
